Job Description :
Exciting Opportunity for Database Manager to be a subject matter expert for the organization, you will also be involved in exciting Data-intensive projects.
Mandatory Skill(s)
More than 5 yearsof experience inDatabase engineering;
Good expertise in diverse and complex Database environments;
Experience with Relational and Distributed Databases for e.g. SQL , MySQL, PostgreSQL or HANA;
Team and Stakeholder Management experience;
Responsible for Service level agreements or Key Performance Index;
Experience inmonitoring and troubleshooting of database with tools such as Cloudwatch, Cloudtrail, IAM, EMR;
Exposure to Azure and Amazon Web Services e.g. EC2, RDS, EBS, S3;
Desirable Skill(s)
Expertise in Data Modelling and Big Data Architecture.
Responsibilities
Responsible to set upand lead thedatabaseteam in-line with new Data-centric strategies;
As key domain expert in matters related to Databases, Cloud, Big Data, etc;
Work with the team on design, architect, administration andsupport for organization's Databaserequirements;
Risk Management in relation to Data Management;
Involved in crafting the Dataand Governance Strategy for organization;
Handledatabasecapacity planning and performance tuning;
Plan and execute work load tests, backup/recovery, replication anddisaster recovery;
Keep abreast on the latest related to Databases technologies.

